      "rationale": "An independent analyst reviewed all boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and post-processing scripts. No errors were identified. Checklist-based review protocol was applied per internal SOP."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selection justified for the flow regime of the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is selected based on its validated performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model is applied consistently with published FDA benchmark studies."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis performed for key uncertain inputs (viscosity, pump clearance gap); influence on NIH quantified.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis over ±10% perturbations of blood viscosity and impeller tip clearance shows NIH variation of less than 8%, within acceptable bounds. Inputs are considered sufficiently characterized for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used for validation are representative of the blood analog and pump geometry class in the COU.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data were collected using a glycerin-water blood analog at hematocrit-equivalent viscosity. Three replicate pump specimens were tested. Sample representativeness for the CPB COU is considered adequate."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that input parameters used in the validation model are equivalent to those of the clinical COU device.",
      "rationale": "This factor was not formally assessed on the grounds that the FDA generic pump geometry is considered sufficiently similar to the target CPB device for the purposes of this COU, and that a formal equivalency mapping was therefore deemed unnecessary. The assessment team concluded that differences in impeller diameter and volute geometry do not materially affect hemolysis prediction fidelity. However, no quantitative equivalency analysis was performed and the factor remains not-assessed rather than documented as not-applicable, leaving the degree of input parameter alignment between the validation model and the COU device unverified at Model Risk Level 3."
    }
